---
title: Sesame-Crusted Chicken Salad with Mandarin Orange & a Peanut Dressing
description: When it comes to salad, we want more than a pile of greens. We’re looking for something bursting with flavor, contrasting textures, you know, some pizzazz! That’s why we’re excited about this main course spinach salad that’s chock-full of satisfying ingredients. We’re talking chicken coated with sesame seeds and seared till tender, crisp carrot ribbons, and juicy, tangy mandarin oranges. A topping of chopped cashews adds more crunch while the homemade peanut dressing gives the dish a crowd-pleasing richness. THIS is a salad we can look forward to.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sesame-crusted-chicken-salad-198ad752.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sesame-crusted-chicken-salad-61b8aba493246e43ea6cd9fd-3bebdceb.pdf
servings: 2
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
  fat: 45 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 25 g
  sugar: 12 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 870 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sesame-crusted-chicken-salad-61b8aba493246e43ea6cd9fd
cuisine: Asian
